The paper deals with the analysis of the asymptotic behavior of wide networks, which is a topic closely related to machine learning and neural networks. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses stochastic gradient descent, which falls under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The use of Feynman diagrams suggests a connection to theoretical physics, which could place the paper in cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.SI (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper presents closed-form expressions for higher-order terms, which could be relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
